.TH "si476x_core_send_command" 9 "si476x_core_send_command" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
si476x_core_send_command \- sends a command to si476x and waits its response
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" si476x_core_send_command
.BI "(struct si476x_core *core "  ","
.BI "const u8 command "  ","
.BI "const u8 args[] "  ","
.BI "const int argn "  ","
.BI "u8 resp[] "  ","
.BI "const int respn "  ","
.BI "const int usecs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "core" 12
si476x_device structure for the device we are
communicating with
.IP "command" 12
command id
.IP "args" 12
command arguments we are sending
.IP "argn" 12
actual size of \fIargs\fP
.IP "resp" 12
buffer to place the expected response from the device
.IP "respn" 12
actual size of \fIresp\fP
.IP "usecs" 12
amount of time to wait before reading the response (in
usecs)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Function returns 0 on succsess and negative error code on
failure
